01:01:27,460 --> 01:01:29,140
in a mechanical fashion.

1058
01:01:30,140 --> 01:01:32,100
And we can't, it's a fact.

1059
01:01:32,100 --> 01:01:35,300
Science just gave up the task of trying to.

1060
01:01:36,260 --> 01:01:39,620
Galileo through Newton and Leibniz,

1061
01:01:39,620 --> 01:01:42,540
science was trying to develop a picture

1062
01:01:42,540 --> 01:01:47,100
of an intelligible world that was given up.

1063
01:01:47,100 --> 01:01:49,180
We don't try to do that anymore.

1064
01:01:49,180 --> 01:01:53,780
We try to find intelligible theories of the world,

1065
01:01:53,780 --> 01:01:55,620
like Newton's theory,

1066
01:01:55,620 --> 01:02:00,620
or the theory of how hydrogen and oxygen molecules

1067
01:02:01,820 --> 01:02:04,740
yield water, but it's not intelligible.

1068
01:02:04,740 --> 01:02:08,560
We can't, we have no grasp of what's going on.

1069
01:02:08,560 --> 01:02:10,740
We understand the theory, we can follow it,

1070
01:02:10,740 --> 01:02:12,520
as you say, we predicted.

1071
01:02:12,520 --> 01:02:16,860
That's now the goal of science for hundreds of years,

1072
01:02:16,860 --> 01:02:19,420
since basically since Newton,

1073
01:02:19,420 --> 01:02:22,100
which abandoned the Galilean hope

1074
01:02:22,100 --> 01:02:26,900
of developing an intelligible world.

1075
01:02:26,900 --> 01:02:30,180
So can you do that for the mind?

1076
01:02:32,700 --> 01:02:34,140
No reason why.

1077
01:02:34,140 --> 01:02:36,340
Maybe we can't, maybe we don't have

1078
01:02:36,340 --> 01:02:39,300
the intellectual capacity to do it,

1079
01:02:39,300 --> 01:02:42,060
but that doesn't mean there's no explanation for it.

1080
01:02:43,060 --> 01:02:47,580
I mean, we're not angels, we're organisms.

1081
01:02:47,580 --> 01:02:52,580
Our mental capacities have certain scope, certain limits,

1082
01:02:53,780 --> 01:02:57,260
but no reason to believe that we can understand everything.

1083
01:02:57,260 --> 01:02:59,100
So in the philosophy of science,

1084
01:02:59,100 --> 01:03:02,540
would you classify yourself as an anti-realist

1085
01:03:02,540 --> 01:03:07,540
in the sense that we have access to empirical information,

1086
01:03:07,820 --> 01:03:10,620
we can sense regularities,

1087
01:03:10,620 --> 01:03:14,620
but there's really no hope of understanding reality

1088
01:03:14,620 --> 01:03:17,140
as it is quite reality in itself.

1089
01:03:17,140 --> 01:03:18,100
No, I don't.

1090
01:03:18,100 --> 01:03:20,340
We can understand it to the extent

1091
01:03:20,340 --> 01:03:22,980
that humans are capable of understanding things.

1092
01:03:24,260 --> 01:03:27,300
We are, I don't know about you,

1093
01:03:27,300 --> 01:03:31,780
but I have no grasp of,

1094
01:03:31,780 --> 01:03:35,940
I can follow the theory that explains how hydrogen

1095
01:03:36,740 --> 01:03:40,460
oxygen end up feeling like a liquid,

1096
01:03:40,460 --> 01:03:42,220
but I don't have any grasp of it.

1097
01:03:42,220 --> 01:03:45,060
I can follow the theory, okay?

1098
01:03:45,060 --> 01:03:47,100
And that's the way science works.

1099
01:03:48,100 --> 01:03:52,740
I have no grasp of it, field of force, let's say.

1100
01:03:52,740 --> 01:03:57,020
I understand it can work with vector spaces and so on,

1101
01:03:57,020 --> 01:04:01,540
but that doesn't give me what Tom Nagel

1102
01:04:01,540 --> 01:04:03,580
calls a feeling of what it is.

1103
01:04:04,580 --> 01:04:07,620
We don't have a feeling of that about anything,

1104
01:04:09,420 --> 01:04:13,780
but we can do the best we can to try to find theories

1105
01:04:13,780 --> 01:04:17,660
that explain the properties that we discovered.

1106
01:04:17,660 --> 01:04:21,580
Now we can understand the theories, maybe get better ones.

1107
01:04:21,580 --> 01:04:25,100
Can we get good enough ones to explain,

1108
01:04:25,100 --> 01:04:27,820
say, elements of consciousness?

1109
01:04:27,820 --> 01:04:29,340
You never know.

1110
01:04:29,340 --> 01:04:32,860
You can, you know, as you learn and study more,

1111
01:04:32,980 --> 01:04:36,180
you find more, then you find more problems.

1112
01:04:36,180 --> 01:04:38,980
Not science, you know, it's like hill climbing.

1113
01:04:38,980 --> 01:04:42,060
You climb a hill, you think you've gotten somewhere,

1114
01:04:42,060 --> 01:04:44,660
you look up and there's a big hill.

1115
01:04:44,660 --> 01:04:46,940
It's all the whole history of science.

1116
01:04:46,940 --> 01:04:49,060
No, one of the questions we'd love to ask

1117
01:04:49,060 --> 01:04:52,940
on Close to the Truth is a two-word question,

1118
01:04:52,940 --> 01:04:56,340
two-word sentence, what exists?

1119
01:04:56,340 --> 01:05:00,940
And by that, what we mean are what are the minimum number

1120
01:05:00,940 --> 01:05:04,460
